d/head-to-head |title=Republic of Ireland \u2013 Head to Head Data |publisher=statto.com |accessdate=5 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714125103/http://www.statto.com/football/teams/international/republic-of-ireland/head-to-head |archivedate=14 July 2014 }}</ref> The only [[UEFA]] members against whom Ireland have not played are: [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]], [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]], [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] and [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]].\n\n{{updated|14 November 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 100%;\"\n|-\n! Against\n! Region\n! {{abbr|P|Played}}\n! {{abbr|W|Won}}\n! {{abbr|D|Drawn}}\n! {{abbr|L|Lost}}\n! {{abbr|GF|Goals for}}\n! {{abbr|GA|Goals against}}\n! {{abbr|GD|Goal difference}}\n! Win %\n! First match\n! Last match\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|ALB}} || UEFA || 4 || 3 || 1 || 0 || 6 || 2 || +4 || {{#expr:3/4*100 round 2}}% || {{dts|format=dmy|1992|05|26}} || 7 June 2003\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|ALG}} || CAF || 2 || 1 || 0 || 1 || 3 || 2 || +1 || {{#expr:1/2*100 round 2}}% || {{dts|format=dmy|1982|04|28}} || 29 May 2010\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|AND}} || UEFA || 4 || 4 || 0 || 0 || 11 || 2 || +9 || {{#expr:4/4*100 round 2}}% || {{dts|format=dmy|2001|03|28}} || 7 October 2011\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|ARG}} || CONMEBOL || 4 || 0 || 0 || 4 || 0 || 5 || \u22125 || {{#expr:0/4*100 round 2}}% || {{dts|format=dmy|1951|05|13}} || 11 August 2010\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|ARM}} || UEFA || 2 || 2 || 0 || 0 || 3 || 1 || +2 || {{#expr:2/2*100 round 2}}% || {{dts|format=dmy|2010|09|03}} || 11 October 2011\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|AUS}} || AFC || 2 || 1 || 0 || 1 || 2 || 4 || \u22122 || {{#expr:1/2*100 round 2}}% || {{dts|format=dmy|2003|08|19}} || 12 August 2009\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|AUT}} || UEF