, the team played a 1\u20131 away draw against world champions, Germany, when a goal by [[John O'Shea]] won Ireland a late point in the 94th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/soccer/2014/1014/652368-germany-ireland/|title=O'Shea's 'fairytale ending' secures draw|publisher=RT\u00c9 Sport|date=14 October 2014}}</ref> They then suffered their first defeat of the campaign to Scotland; losing 1\u20130, before scoring another late goal through Shane Long to make it 1\u20131 and earn a well-deserved point against Poland at home. They then drew 1\u20131 at home to Scotland, before winning 3 games in a row against Gibraltar, Georgia and Germany; 4\u20130, 1\u20130 and 1\u20130 respectively. Shane Long scored the memorable winner against the World Champions Germany. However, in their last group game, they lost 2\u20131 away to Poland and missed out on an qualifying spot, finishing third in the group and advancing to the [[play-offs]]. They were drawn against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in the play-offs. They drew the first leg away 1\u20131, and won the second leg 2\u20130, winning 3\u20131 on aggregate and qualifying for [[UEFA Euro 2016]] in France.\n\n===Schedule===\n{{updated|18 November 2019}}\n<small>Republic of Ireland goal tally first.</small><ref>{{cite web|title=Senior Men Matches|url=http://www.fai.ie/ireland/senior-men/matches |publisher=Football Association of Ireland|accessdate=12 November 2016}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Date\n! Competition\n! Venue\n! Opponent\n! Result\n! Scorers\n|-style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| 7 June 2019\n| UEFA Euro 2020 Qualification\n| Copenhagen, Denmark\n|align=left|{{fb|Denmark}}\n| 1\u20131\n|align=left |[[Pierre-Emile H\u00f8jbjerg]] {{goal|}}, [[Shane Duffy]] {{goal|85}}\n|-style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| 10 June 2019\n| UEFA Euro 2020 Qualification\n| Dublin, Ireland\n|align=left|{{fb|Gibraltar}}\n| 2\u20130\n|align=left |[[Joseph Chipolina]] {{goal|29|o.g.}}, [[Robbie Brady]] {{goal|90+3}}\n|-style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| 5 September 2019\n| UEFA Euro 2020 Qualification\n| Dublin, Ireland\n|align=left|{{fb|Switzerland}}\n| 1\u20131\n|align=left|[[Fabian Sch\u00e4r]] {{goal|74}}, [[David McGoldrick]] {{goal|85}}\n|-style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| 10 September 2019\n| Friendly match\n| Dublin, Ireland\n|align=left|{{fb|Bulgaria}}\n| 3\u20131\n|align=left |[[Alan Browne (footballer)|Alan Browne]] {{goal|56}}, [[Ivelin Popov]] {{goal|67|pen.}}, [[Kevin Long (footballer)|Kevin Long]] {{goal|83}}, [[James Collins (footballer, born 1990)|James Collins]] {{goal|86}}\n|-style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| 12 October 2019\n| UEFA Euro 2020 Qualification\n| Tbilisi, Georgia\n|align=left|{{fb|Georgia}}\n|0\u20130\n|\n|-style=\"background:#fbb\"\n| 15 October 2019\n| UEFA Euro 2020 Qualification\n| Geneva, Switzerland\n|align=left|{{fb|Switzerland}}\n|0\u20132\n|align=left |[[Haris Seferovi\u0107]] {{goal|16}}, [[Edimilson Fernandes]] {{goal|90+3}}\n|-style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| 14 November 2019\n| Friendly match\n| Dublin, Ireland\n|align=left|{{fb|New Zealand}}\n|3\u20131\n|align=left |[[Callum McCowatt]] {{goal|30}}, [[Derrick Williams (footballer)|Derrick Williams]] {{goal|45}}, [[Sean Maguire (footballer)|Sean Maguire]] {{goal|52}}, [[Callum Robinson]] {{goal|75}}\n|-style=\"background:#ffc\"\n| 18 November 2019\n| UEFA Euro 2020 Qualification\n| Dublin, Ireland\n|align=left|{{fb|Denmark}}\n|1\u20131\n|align=left |[[Martin Braithwaite]] {{goal|73}}, [[Matt Doherty (footballer, born 1992)|Matt Doherty]] {{goal|85}}\n|-style=\"backgroumd:#ffc\"\n|TBD\n| [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying play-offs|UEFA Euro 2020 Play-Offs]]\n| Bratislava, Slovakia\n|align=left|{{fb|Slovakia}}\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==Player records==\n[[File:Keanoirelandedit.jpg|thumb|right|[[Robbie Keane]]|Robbie Keane, top goalscorer and the most-capped player]]\n[[File:Shay Given.jpg|thumb|right|[[Shay Given]]|Shay Given, most-capped goalkeeper and the second-most capped player]]\n{{legend|#CCFFCC|Players still active are highlighted in green|border=#AAAAAA}}\n\n===Most caps===\n{{updated|18 November 2019|<ref name=\"rsssf\">[http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/ier-recintlp.html#goals Ireland \u2013 Record International Players] Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation. Retrieved 5 September 2015.</ref>}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!#\n! style=\"width:160px;\"| Player\n!National<br>career\n!Caps\n!Goals\n|-\n|1.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Robbie|Keane}}\n|1998\u20132016\n|'''146'''\n|68\n|-\n|2.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Shay|Given}}\n|1996\u20132016\n|'''134'''\n|0\n|-\n|3.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|John|O'Shea||Oshea, John}}\n|2001\u20132018\n|'''118'''\n|3\n|-\n|4.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Kevin|Kilbane}}\n|1997\u20132011\n|'''110'''\n|8\n|-\n|5.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Steve|Staunton}}\n|1988\u20132002\n|'''102'''\n|7\n|-\n|6.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Damien|Duff}}\n|1998\u20132012\n|'''100'''\n|8\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n|7.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Aiden|McGeady}}\n|2004\u2013\n|'''93'''\n|5\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|8.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Niall|Quinn}}\n|1986\u20132002\n|'''91'''\n|21\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Glenn|Whelan}}\n|2008\u2013\n|'''91\n|2\n|-\n|10.\n|align=\"left\"|{{sortname|Tony|Cascarino}}\n|1985\u20132000\n|'''88'''\n|19\n|}\n\n=== Most goals ===\n{{updated|18 November 2019|<ref name=\"rsssf\"/>}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!#\n! style=\"width:160px;\"| Player\n!National career\n!Goals\n!Caps\n!Average\n|-\n|1.\n|align=left| {{sortname|Robbie|Keane}} <small>([[List of international goals scored by Robbie Keane|list]])</small>\n|1998\u20132016\n|'''68'''\n|146\n|{{Decimals|68/146|2}}\n|-\n|2.\n|align=left| {{sortname|Niall|Quinn}}\n|1986\u20132002\n|'''21'''\n|91\n|{{Decimals|21/91|2}}\n|-\n|3.\n|align=left| {{sortname|Frank|Stapleton}}\n|1977\u201390\n|'''20'''\n|71\n|{{Decimals|20/71|2}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|4.\n|align=left| {{sortname|Don|Givens}}\n|1969\u201381\n|'''19'''\n|56\n|{{Decimals|19/56|2}}\n|-\n|align=left| {{sortname|John|Aldridge}}\n|1986\u201397\n|'''19'''\n|69\n|{{Decimals|19/69|2}}\n|-\n|align=left| {{sortname|Tony|Cascarino}}\n|1985\u20132000\n|'''19'''\n|88\n|{{Decimals|19/88|2}}\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n|7.\n|align=\"left\"| {{sortname|Shane|Long}}\n|2007\u2013\n|'''17'''\n|82\n|{{Decimals|17/82|2}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|8.\n|align=left| {{sortname|Noel|Cantwell}}\n|1953\u201367\n|'''14'''\n|36\n|{{Decimals|14/36|2}}\n|-\n|align=left| {{sortname|Jonathan|Walters}}\n|2010\u201318\n|'''14'''\n|54\n|{{Decimals|14/54|2}}\n|-\n|align=left| {{sortname|Kevin|Doyle}}\n|2006\u201317\n|'''14'''\n|63\n|{{Decimals|14/63|2}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|11.\n|align=left| {{sortname|Jimmy|Dunne}}\n|1930\u201339\n|'''13'''\n|15\n|{{Decimals|13/15|2}}\n|-\n|align=left| {{sortname|Gerry|Daly}}\n|1973\u201386\n|'''13'''\n|48\n|{{Decimals|13/48|2}}\n|}\n\n==Managers==\nBetween 1921 and 1969, a committee of selectors chose the team, on occasions a coach or team manager was appointed; [[Mick Meagan]] was the first manager to actually select the team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fai.ie/international/senior-men/irelands-managers.html |title=Ireland's Senior Team Managers |publisher=Football Association of Ireland |date=3 February 2010 |accessdate=3 February 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008033506/http://www.fai.ie/international/senior-men/irelands-managers.html |archivedate=8 October 2011 }}</ref> Managers from the periods in which the national side was known as the ''Irish Free State'' or simply ''Ireland'' are obscure and many are not currently known, however it is known that [[Val Harris]], [[Bill Lacey (footballer)|Bill Lacey]] and [[Alex Stevenson]] managed the side.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fai.ie/domestic/news/fai-history-1930-1959 |title=FAI History: 1930 \u2013 1959 |publisher=Football Association of Ireland |date=5 June 2009 |accessdate=25 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Managerial Records===\n{{updated|18 November 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=155|Manager\n!Career\n!P\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!GF\n!GA\n!GD\n!Win %\n!Loss %\n! Notes\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Doug|Livingstone}}\n|1951\u20131953\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRL}} {{sortname|Alex|Stevenson}}\n|1953\u20131955\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRL}} {{sortname|Johnny|Carey}}\n|1955\u20131967 \n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|Reached quarter-final stage of [[1964 European Nations' Cup]]\n|- \n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRL}} {{sortname|Noel|Cantwell}}\n|1967\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRL}} {{sortname|Charlie|Hurley}}\n|1967\u20131969\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|?\n|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRE}} {{sortname|Mick|Meagan}}\n|1969\u20131971\n|12\n|0\n|3\n|9\n|7\n|26\n|\u221219\n|{{#expr:0/12*100 round 1}}%\n|{{#expr:9/12*100 round 1}}%\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRE}} {{sortname|Liam|Tuohy|Liam Tuohy (footballer)}}\n|1971\u20131973\n|10\n|3\n|1\n|6\n|11\n|20\n|\u22129\n|{{#expr:3/10*100 round 1}}%\n|{{#expr:6/10*100 round 1}}%\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRE}} {{sortname|Se\u00e1n|Thomas}}\n|1973\n|1\n|0\n|1\n|0\n|1\n|1\n|0\n|{{#expr:0/1*100 round 1}}%\n|{{#expr:0/1*100 round 1}}%\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|Caretaker\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{flagicon|IRE}} {{sortname|Johnny|Giles}}\n|1973\u20131980\n|36\n|13\n|9\n|14\n|48\n|45\n|3\n|{{#expr:13/36*100 round 1}}%\n|{{#expr:14/36*100 round 1}}%\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"