{"title_page": "List of best-selling video game franchises", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n<!--\nNOTE TO ARTICLE EDITORS:\nIf you are updating the sales figures for a franchise, please remember to include a citation that confirms the sales. Note that, as mentioned on the talk page, VGChartz is considered by a consensus to be an unreliable source for sales figures, and thus should not be linked to on this article.\n\nAlso note this list's incredible length and complex formatting used throughout the article, which understandably may be difficult for less-experienced users to handle. If you have any issues with the list, please leave a comment on the talk page.\n<ref>{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |date=January 9, 2017 |url=https://gematsu.com/2018/01/media-create-sales-12-25-17-12-31-17 |title=Media Create Sales: 12/25/17 \u2013 12/31/17 |publisher=Gematsu |accessdate=January 13, 2017}}</ref>\nThank you.\n-->{{Video Games}}\nThis is a list of [[List of video game franchises|video game franchises]] that have sold or shipped at least five million copies. Unless otherwise stated, numbers indicate worldwide units sold, ordered alphabetically whenever two or more list the same amount. The exception are the ones specifying shipments, which have lower precedence than others listing sales.\n\n[[Media franchise|Franchise]] sales include [[Expansion pack#Video game expansion packs|expansion packs]] even though they are not considered full [[video game]]s. [[Free-to-play]] game downloads (including free [[mobile game]]s) and [[microtransaction]]s should not figure into sales or shipment figures. For best-selling individual video games, see the [[list of best-selling video games]]. The sales figures given below do not include [[arcade game]] sales, which can be found at the [[list of highest-grossing arcade games]]. For the franchises that have generated the most revenue, see the [[list of highest-grossing video game franchises]].\n\n== At least 100 million copies ==\n{{Color box|#FFFFBF;|border=darkgray}} \u2013 This color indicates a sub-series of a larger video game franchise. This does not necessarily apply for series that are not video game-based.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:33.4%;\"| [[list of video game franchises|Franchise name]]\n! style=\"width:33.3%;\"| Original release date\n! style=\"width:33.3%;\"| Sales\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|''[[Mario (franchise)|Mario]]'' || [[1981 in video games|July 9, 1981]] || {{#expr:344.38+145.14+52.250.725+41.06+24.459+32.624 round 2}} million\n* ''[[Super Mario]]'' series: 344.38{{nbsp}}million<ref group=\"n\" name=\"SuperMario\"/>\n* ''[[Mario Kart]]'' series: 145.14{{nbsp}}million<ref group=\"n\" name=\"MarioKart\"/>\n* ''[[Mario Party]]'' series: 52,250,725<ref group=\"n\" name=\"MarioParty\"/><ref name=\"Romano\"/><ref>{{cite web|date=December 16, 2016|title=This Week In Sales: Yakuza 6 Pummels Its Way To The Top|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2016/12/16/week-sales-yakuza-6-pummels-way-top/|website=Siliconera.com|accessdate=25 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Romano\">{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Sal |date=January 9, 2017 |url=https://gematsu.com/2018/01/media-create-sales-12-25-17-12-31-17 |title=Media Create Sales: 12/25/17 \u2013 12/31/17 |publisher=Gematsu |accessdate=January 13, 2017}}</ref>\n* ''[[List of Mario sports games|Mario Sports]]'' series: 41.06{{nbsp}}million<ref group=\"n\" name=\"MarioSports\"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Romano  |first=Sal |date=May 24, 2017 |url=http://gematsu.com/2017/05/media-create-sales-51517-52117 |title=Media Create Sales: 5/15/17 \u2013 5/21/17 |publisher=Gematsu |accessdate=May 25, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Nunneley\">{{Cite web | url = https://www.vg247.com/2019/07/30/switch-sales-36-87-million-lifetime/ | title = Switch lifetime sales hit 36.87 million, Super Mario Maker 2 hits 2.42 million units sold \u2013 Nintendo Q1 | first = Stephany | last = Nunneley | date = July 30,