f/2011/110426e.pdf#page=5|title=Supplementary Information about Earnings Release|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|date=2011-04-26|format=PDF|accessdate=2011-04-26|page=10}}</ref>\n** 3DS port: 1.52 million<ref>http://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2014/140508e.pdf</ref>\n* ''[[Donkey Kong Country: Tropical Freeze]]'': 130.000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/nintendo-s-wii-u-and-3ds-see-strong-february-sales-over-last-year/1100-6418305/|title=Nintendo's Wii U and 3DS see strong February sales over last year|publisher=}}</ref>\n** Switch port: 2.25 million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2019/190131_2e.pdf/|title=Earnings Release for the Nine-Month Period Ended December 2018|publisher=Nintendo}}</ref>\n|group=n|name=DonkeyKong}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2019/190425_3e.pdf|title=Earnings Release for Fiscal Year Ended March 2019 - Supplementary Information|date=March 31, 2019|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref>\n|group=n|name=MarioFranchise}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| [[Mario]] first appeared in 1981 in the original ''[[Donkey Kong (video game)|Donkey Kong]]'',<ref name=\"mario2\">{{cite press release | url=http://www.newswire.ca/en/releases/mmnr/Super_Mario_Galaxy/index.html | title=Italian plumber more memorable than Harper, Dion | publisher=[[Nintendo]] | date=2007-11-13 | accessdate=2008-01-12 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090911224500/http://www.newswire.ca/en/releases/mmnr/Super_Mario_Galaxy/index.html | archivedate=2009-09-11 }}</ref> before starring in ''[[Mario Bros.]]'', followed by the ''[[Super Mario]]'' series of [[platform game]]s. The character was created by Japanese game designer [[Shigeru Miyamoto]] and has since become the official mascot of [[Nintendo]], owner of the trademark. It is developed by various Nintendo studios. The ''Mario'' franchise has expanded into other [[video game genres|game genres]], including [[racing video game|racing]], [[sports game|sports]], [[party video game|party]], [[puzzle video game|puzzle]], and [[role-playing video game|role-playing games]]. The franchise includes other media, including [[List of Mario television series|three animated television series]], comic books, a [[manga]], a [[Super Mario Bros. (film)|film]] and other merchandise. It is currently the best-selling video game franchise of all time.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|''[[Pok\u00e9mon (video game series)|Pok\u00e9mon]]'' || [[1996 in video games|February 27, 1996]] || 362.06{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pokemon.co.jp/corporate/en/services/|title=Pok\u00e9mon in Figures|website=[[The Pok\u00e9mon Company]]|date=December 2019|accessdate=Dec 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2020/200130_3e.pdf|title=Million Sellers Titles of Nintendo Products|page=7|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref><!--Please note that, as per the mention of free-to-play downloads on the top of the article, the millions of downloads of Pok\u00e9mon Go should not figure into the franchise's sales. --><!--The 346 figure is as of September 2019, adding how much Sword and Shield sold(16.06) the numbers are now at 362.06 copies sold -->\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''[[Pok\u00e9mon]]'' was created by [[Satoshi Tajiri]], founder and president of [[Game Freak]], in 1996 as a [[role-playing video game]] for the [[Game Boy]] [[handheld game console]], soon turning into [[List of highest-grossing media franchises|the highest-grossing media franchise]] of all time. The franchise as a whole includes an [[Pok\u00e9mon (anime)|anime series]], [[List of Pok\u00e9mon manga|various manga]], a [[Pok\u00e9mon Trading Card Game|trading card game]], toys, merchandise, books, [[List of Pok\u00e9mon films|over twenty films]] (one of the [[List of highest-grossing anime films#Highest-grossing anime film franchises and film series|highest-grossing animated film series]]), and other media. It is produced by [[The Pok\u00e9mon Company]], which is a joint venture by the three companies holding the rights to ''Pok\u00e9mon'': [[Nintendo]], [[Game Freak]], and [[Creatures (company)|Creatures]], while Nintendo owns the trademark.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| style=\"background:#FFFFBF;\"| ''[[Super Mario]]'' || [[1985 in video games|September 13, 1985]] || 344.38{{nbsp}}million{{#tag:ref|''Super Mario'' series:\n* Up until September 2015 {{ndash}} 310{{nbsp}}million+<ref name=\"Nintendo\">{{cite press release |url=https://www.nintendo.com/whatsnew/detail/vy8mvC_LJPHnlpBFTR5w-BYV1FP_m7hN |title= Super Mario Maker has sold 1 Million units around the world|publisher=[[Nintendo]] |date=September 30, 2015 |accessdate=2016-01-15}}</ref>\n* October 2015 to March 2016 {{ndash}} {{#expr:3.52-1.88}}{{nbsp}}million<ref name=\"march2016\"/><ref name=\"sep15\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2015/151028_3e.pdf#page=5|title=September 2015}}</ref>\n* April 2016 to March 2017  {{ndash}} {{#expr:2.34+1.03}}{{nbsp}}million<ref name=\"march2017\">{{cite news |title=Earnings Release for Fiscal Year Ended March 2017 |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2017/170427_6e.pdf |publisher=[[Nintendo]] |date=April 27, 2017}}</ref>\n* ''[[New Super Mario Bros. 2]]'' sales from April 2017 to March 2019 {{ndash}} {{#expr:13.16-11.27}}{{nbsp}}million<ref name=\"nintendo-software\">{{cite web |title=Sales Data - Top Selling Title Sales Units |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/index.html |website=IR Information |publisher=[[Nintendo]] |accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sales Data - Top Selling Title Sales Units |url=http://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/3ds.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709085422/http://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/3ds.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2017-07-09 |website=IR Information |publisher=[[Nintendo]] |accessdate=2017-07-09}}</ref>\n* ''[[Super Mario Odyssey]]'' (released October 2017) {{ndash}} 16.59{{nbsp}}million<ref name=\"nintendo-software\"/><ref name=\"Nunneley\" /><ref name=\"gematsu.com\">{{Cite web | url = https://gematsu.com/2019/10/switch-worldwide-sales-top-41-67-million-he-legend-of-zelda-links-awakening-sales-top-3-13-million | title = Switch worldwide sales top 41.67 million, he Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening sales top 3.13 million | first = Sal | last = Romano | date = October 31, 2019 | accessdate = October 31, 2019 | work = Gematsu }}</ref>\n* ''[[New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe]]'' (2019) {{ndash}} 5.85{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/index.html|title=IR Information : Sales Data - Top Selling Title Sales Units|website=Nintendo|date=September 30, 2019|accessdate=December 16, 2019}}</ref>\n* ''[[Super Mario Maker 2]]'' (2019) {{ndash}} 5.04{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{cite web |title=Earnings Release for Three-Month Period Ended June 2019 - Supplementary Information |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2019/190730_2e.pdf|website=Nintendo, Co. Ltd. |publisher=Nintendo, Co. Ltd. |accessdate=July 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Top Selling Title Sales Units |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/index.html|website=Nintendo, Co. Ltd. |publisher=Nintendo, Co. Ltd. |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|group=n|name=SuperMario}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Earnings Release for the Nine-Month Period Ended December 2019 |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2020/200130_3e.pdf |website=Nintendo, Co. Ltd. |publisher=Nintendo, Co. Ltd. |accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| The {{Nihongo foot|''Super Mario''|\u30b9\u30fc\u30d1\u30fc\u30de\u30ea\u30aa|S\u016bp\u0101 Mario}} series of [[platform game]]s began in 1985 and features the character, Mario. The ''Super Mario'' series forms the core of the ''Mario'' franchise.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Call of Duty]]'' || [[2003 in video games|October 29, 2003]] || 300 million<ref>[https://gamingbolt.com/call-of-duty-series-crosses-300-million-lifetime-sales Call of Duty Series Crosses 300 Million Lifetime Sales]. \"Activision announced at their recent quarterly financial meeting (via Niko Partners senior analyst Daniel Ahmad on Twitter) that the Call of Duty franchise has now collectively sold over 300 million units across the world.\" May 2019.</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''Call of Duty'' is a series of [[first-person shooter]] video games. The series is published by [[Activision]] and [[Aspyr Media]] and developed by [[Infinity Ward]], [[Gray Matter Interactive]], [[Treyarch]], [[Sledgehammer Games]], [[Raven Software]], [[Neversoft]] and [[High Moon Studios]]. With new games in the series released annually to blockbuster-level sales, the series is verified by the [[Guinness World Records]] as the best-selling first-person shooter game series. It is also the most successful video game franchise created in the [[United States]] and is the best-selling video game franchise not owned by Nintendo. In addition to main series sales, there have been over 100 million downloads of the mobile spin-off, ''[[Call of Duty: Mobile]]''.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\" |\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|''[[Grand Theft Auto]]''||[[1997 in video games|October 21, 1997]]|| 300 million<ref>{{cite web|title=''Grand Theft Auto'' life-time sales hit 250 million, GTA 5 and GTA Online ships 70 million units|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.uk/grand-theft-auto-life-time-sales-hits-250-million-gta-5-gta-online-ships-70-million-units-1589687|website=www.ibtimes.co.uk|date=3 November 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"variety.com\">{{cite web|title=More Than 100 Million Copies of 'GTA V' Sold, 'GTA Online' Continues to Thrive|url=https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/gta-v-100-million-sales-1203022310/|web