elda3ds\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2014/05/07/zelda-link-worlds-super-mario-3d-world/|title=How Did Zelda: A Link Between Worlds And Super Mario 3D World Do?|date=2014-05-07}}</ref><ref name=\"zelda-sales-breath\">{{cite news |last1=McFerran |first1=Damien |title=Zelda: Breath Of The Wild Is The Best-Selling Zelda Game Of All Time, Kind Of |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2018/04/zelda_breath_of_the_wild_is_the_best-selling_zelda_game_of_all_time_kind_of |accessdate=21 April 2019 |work=Nintendo Life |publisher=Gamer Network |date=26 April 2018}}</ref>\n** ''[[The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds]]'' - 2.51 million<ref name=\"zelda3ds\"/>\n** ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Wind Waker HD]]'' - 2.3{{nbsp}}million<ref name=\"wii_u\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/sales/software/wiiu.html|title=IR Information : Sales Data - Top Selling Software Sales Units - Wii U Software|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref>\n** ''[[Hyrule Warriors]]'' - 1 million<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2015/01/koei_tecmo_releases_awesome_hyrule_warriors_wallpapers_to_celebrate_one_million_units_shipped |title=Koei Tecmo Releases Awesome Hyrule Warriors Wallpapers to Celebrate One Million Units Shipped |last=Whitehead |first=Thomas |date=January 27, 2015 |website=Nintendo Life |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150127194455/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2015/01/koei_tecmo_releases_awesome_hyrule_warriors_wallpapers_to_celebrate_one_million_units_shipped |archivedate=January 27, 2015 |url-status=live |accessdate=January 27, 2015}}</ref>\n** ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Majora's Mask 3D]]'' - 2.03 million<ref>https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2015/150507_4e.pdf</ref>\n** ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Tri Force Heroes]]'' - 1.14 million<ref name=\"march2016\"/>\n** ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Twilight Princess HD]]'' - 59.987<ref>{{cite web |last=Sato |date=March 16, 2016 |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2016/03/16/week-sales-division-raids-twilight-princess-hd-summon-night-6-follows/ |title=This Week In Sales: The Division Raids In, Twilight Princess HD And Summon Night 6 Follows|publisher=Siliconera |accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Sato |date=March 23, 2016 |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2016/03/23/week-sales-pokkn-tournament-brings-fight-digimon-world-follows/ |title=This Week In Sales: Pokk\u00e9n Tournament Brings The Fight, Digimon World Follows|publisher=Siliconera |accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref>\n** ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild]]'' - {{#expr:16.34+1.5}}{{nbsp}}million<ref name=\"nintendo-software\"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Nunneley|first=Stephany|title=Switch sales stand at over 17M units, Breath of the Wild now best-selling Zelda title|url=https://www.vg247.com/2018/04/26/switch-sales-over-17m-units-breath-of-the-wild/|website=VG247|accessdate=April 27, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426211952/http://www.vg247.com/2018/04/26/switch-sales-over-17m-units-breath-of-the-wild/|archivedate=April 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=2018-04-26}}</ref>\n** ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening (2019 video game)]]'' - 4.19 million<ref name=\"gematsu.com\">{{Cite web | url = https://gematsu.com/2019/10/switch-worldwide-sales-top-41-67-million-he-legend-of-zelda-links-awakening-sales-top-3-13-million | title = Switch worldwide sales top 41.67 million, he Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening sales top 3.13 million | first = Sal | last = Romano | date = October 31, 2019 | accessdate = October 31, 2019 | work = Gematsu }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2020/200130_3e.pdf |title=Earnings Release for the Nine-Month Period Ended December 2019 |date=December 31, 2019 |accessdate=January 30, 2020 |work=[[Nintendo]]}}</ref>\n|group=n|name=Zelda}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| {{nihongo foot|''The Legend of Zelda''|\u30bc\u30eb\u30c0\u306e\u4f1d\u8aac|Zeruda no Densetsu|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} is an [[action-adventure game]] franchise created by Japanese [[game designers]] [[Shigeru Miyamoto]] and [[Takashi Tezuka]]. It is primarily developed and published by [[Nintendo]], although some portable installments and re-releases have been outsourced to [[Capcom]], [[Vanpool (company)|Vanpool]], and [[Grezzo]]. The gameplay incorporates action-adventure and elements of [[action role-playing game]]s.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog]]''|| [[1991 in video games|June 23, 1991]] || 100.54{{nbsp}}million<!--Please note that, as per the mention of free-to-play downloads on the top of the article, the millions of downloads of this franchise's free-to-play games should not figure into the franchise's sales.-->{{#tag:ref|The ''Sonic'' franchise had sold 70{{nbsp}}million units (89{{nbsp}}million including the ''Mario & Sonic'' series) by March 2011.<ref name=\"sega2011\">{{cite book |title=Annual Report 2011 |date=2011 |page=43 |url=https://www.segasammy.co.jp/english/ir/library/pdf/printing_annual/2011/ssh_ar11e_all_final_1021.pdf#page=45 |accessdate=October 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|title=London's Calling Mario & Sonic |publisher= Sega/Nintendo|date=April 21, 2011| url=http://www.sega.com/news/?n=5048|accessdate=April 21, 2011}})</ref> In addition, the ''[[Mario & Sonic]]'' series sold over 25{{nbsp}}million units {{as of|2019|lc=y}},<ref name=\"linkedin\"/> ''[[Sonic Generations]]'' sold 1.85 million units as of March 2012, ''[[Sonic & All-Stars Racing Transformed]]'' sold 1.36 million units as of March 2013, ''[[Sonic Lost World]]'' sold 710,000 units as of March 2014, and ''[[Sonic Boom: Rise of Lyric]]'' & ''[[Sonic Boom: Shattered Crystal|Shattered Crystal]]'' sold 620,000 units as of March 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.segasammy.co.jp/english/ir/library/pdf/settlement/2012/20120511_hosoku_e_final.pdf|title=Appendix of Consolidated Financial Statements Year Ended M