86288 |accessdate=6 February 2019 |work=Investor Relations |publisher=[[Take-Two Interactive]] |date=6 February 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" |''NBA 2K'' is a series of [[basketball]] [[sports game]]s. Originally published by [[Sega]], under the label Sega Sports, it is now published by [[2K Sports]]. All of the games in the series have been developed by [[Visual Concepts]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Tom Clancy's]]''|| [[1998 in video games|August 21, 1998]] ||82 million<ref name=\"ubisoftgroup\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ubisoftgroup.com/en-us/about_ubisoft/facts_and_figures.aspx |title=Facts & Figures |publisher=[[Ubisoft]] |year=2014 |accessdate=2014-07-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140721012750/http://www.ubisoftgroup.com/en-us/about_ubisoft/facts_and_figures.aspx |archivedate=July 21, 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"tomclancy\">{{cite web | url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/tom-clancy-series-tops-55-million-units-sold | title=Tom Clancy series tops 55 million units sold | date=2008-05-28 | author=Matt Martin | accessdate=2008-11-28 | publisher=[[GamesIndustry.biz]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| Includes sales from Tom Clancy\u2013branded games developed by Ubisoft, including ''[[Tom Clancy's Ghost Recon|Ghost Recon]]'', ''[[Tom Clancy's Rainbow Six|Rainbow Six]]'', ''[[Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell|Splinter Cell]]'', and ''[[Tom Clancy's The Division|The Division]]''.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[List of Star Wars video games|Star Wars]]'' || [[1983 in video games|May 1983]] || 100.371 million{{#tag:ref|''Star Wars'' franchise:\n* ''[[Lego Star Wars]]'' series - 33 million<ref name=\"legostarwars\">{{cite news |last=Spangler |first=Todd |title=Lego 'Star Wars: The Force Awakens' Game to Debut This Summer |url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/games/lego-star-wars-the-force-awake