nary Runtime Environment for Wireless|BREW]] [[Mobile game|mobile]] versions: 30 million downloads in the US ({{cite news|title=Namco Networks' Pac-Man Franchise Surpasses 30 Million Paid Transactions in the United States on Brew|url=http://www.allbusiness.com/technology/software-services-applications-internet/14737270-1.html|accessdate=22 February 2012|agency=[[AllBusiness.com]]|year=2010}})\n* {{cite web|title=Famicom Mini: Pac-Man (Japan sales)|url=http://garaph.info/softwareindividual.php//gid/1565|publisher=Garaph (based on [[Famitsu]] data)|accessdate=17 March 2012|date=2005-07-28}}:\n** ''[[Classic NES Series|Famicom Mini: Pac-Man]]'' (GBA) - 118,679\n* {{cite web|title=Namco (Japan sales, 2000-2006)|url=http://garaph.info/gamesearch.php?publisher=Namco&opt=0|publisher=Garaph (based on [[Famitsu]] data)|accessdate=17 March 2012|date=2005-07-28}}:\n** ''[[Pac-Pix]]'' (DS) - 98,650\n** ''[[Pac 'n Roll]]'' (DS) - 15,268\n|group=n|name=PacMan}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"|{{nihongo foot|''Pac-Man''|\u30d1\u30c3\u30af\u30de\u30f3 Pakkuman|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} is Japanese video game franchise currently owned and published by Bandai Namco Entertainment, formerly Namco. The [[Pac-Man|eponymous first entry]] was released in arcades in 1980 by Namco during the [[golden age of arcade video games]]. Most games in the franchise are [[List of maze video games|maze chase]] games however it has delved into other genres such as platformers, racing and sports.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\" |\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|''[[Red Dead]]''|| [[2004 in video games|May 4, 2004]] || 41.85{{nbsp}}million{{#tag:ref|''Red Dead'' franchise:\n* Up until 2014 {{ndash}} 15.35 million shipped<ref name=\"gta\" />\n* ''[[Red Dead Redemption 2]]'' (2018) {{ndash}} 26.5{{nbsp}}million units<ref name=\"take2\"/>\n|group=n}}<ref name=\"Sales November 2019\">{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/red-dead-redemption-2-gta-5-and-borderlands-3-reac/