itcher'' takes place in a medieval fantasy world and follows the story of Geralt, one of a few remaining \"witchers\" \u2013 traveling monster hunter for hire, gifted with unnatural powers.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\" |\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Guitar Hero]]'' || [[2005 in video games|November 8, 2005]] || 40 million<ref name=\"guitarhero\">{{cite news | url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/finance/2009/1016/1224256786000.html | title=Music rocks gamers | newspaper=[[The Irish Times]] | date=2009-10-16 | accessdate=2009-10-17 | author=Ciara O'Brien}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Guitar Hero'' is a series of [[music video game|music]] and [[rhythm game|rhythm]] video games published by [[RedOctane]] and [[Activision]], and developed by [[Harmonix Music Systems]] from 2005 to 2007 before development duties of the series were transferred to [[Neversoft]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Harry Potter video games|Harry Potter]]'' || [[2001 in video games|November 15, 2001]] || 40 million<ref name=\"harrypotter\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/harry-potter/5768937/Harry-Potter-and-the-Half-Blood-Prince-one-of-the-most-successful-franchises-of-all-time.html | title=Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince: one of the most successful franchises of all time | date=2009-07-08 | accessdate=2009-08-02 | newspaper=The Daily Telegraph | author=Chris Irvine | location=London}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| Based on the ''Harry Potter'' novels by British writer [[J. K. Rowling]], games in the series have been published by Electronic Arts and [[Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Civilization (series)|Civilization]]'' || [[1991 in video games|September 1991]] || 40 million<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://venturebeat.com/2017/05/23/civ-vi-was-a-large-contributor-to-take-twos-net-revenue-growth/ | title = Civ VI was a large contributor to Take-Two's net revenue growth | first = Stephanie | last= Chan | date = May 23, 2017 | accessdate =  May 23, 2017 | work = [[Venture Beat]] }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Civilization'' is a series of [[turn-based strategy]] video games. [[Sid Meier]] developed the first game in the series and has had creative input for most of the rest. The basic gameplay functions are similar throughout the series, namely, guiding a civilization on a macro-scale from prehistory to the present day.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Medal of Honor (video game series)|Medal of Honor]]''|| [[1999 in video games|November 11, 1999]] || 39 million{{#tag:ref|''Medal of Honor'' series:\n* The whole series as of 2007: 31 million<ref name=\"medalofhonor\">{{cite press release | url=http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1013897&newsId=20071120005375&newsLang=en | title=EA Ships Medal Of Honor Airborne For The PlayStation 3 To Store Shelves Nationwide | date=2007-11-20 | accessdate=2009-03-21 | publisher=[[Electronic Arts]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710163602/http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1013897&newsId=20071120005375&newsLang=en |archivedate=2011-07-10}}</ref>\n* [[Medal of Honor (2010 video game)|''Medal of Honor'' (2010)]]: 5 million<ref>{{cite web|title=Electronic Arts Reports Q3 FY11 Financial Results|url=http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1012492&newsId=20110201007369&newsLang=en|website=EA.com|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|accessdate=23 August 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110208174536/http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1012492&newsId=20110201007369&newsLang=en|archivedate=8 February 2011|date=1 February 2011}}</re