. Figure for retail copies only was 6.5 million for standalone ''Half-Life 2'' packages and 3 million as part of ''The Orange Box'' as of December 2008; Remo, 2008. All retail copies of ''Half-Life 2'' also came bundled with a copy of ''[[Counter-Strike: Source]]'', a remake of ''Half-Life: Counter-Strike.'' Thorsen, Tor. [https://www.gamespot.com/articles/valve-readying-half-life-2-bundles-counter-strike-source-available-next-week/1100-6109232/ \"Valve readying Half-Life 2 bundles; Counter-Strike: Source available next week.\"] Gamespot. September 29, 2004</ref>\n*''Half-Life 2: Episode One'' standalone: 1.4 million<ref>Does not include digital sales. Remo, 2008.</ref>\n*''[[The Orange Box]]'': 3 million<ref>''Half-Life 2'', ''Episode One'' and ''Episode Two'' were sold as part of the Orange Box, which is counted as one product here to avoid double-counting; does not include digital. Remo, 2008.</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Half-Life'' is a series of first-person shooter games developed and published by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]]. The games combine shooting combat, puzzles, and storytelling.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Kinect]]'' || [[2010 in video games|October 9, 2010]] || 27 million<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/kinect-sales-reach-24-million/1100-6403766/ |title=Kinect sales reach 24 million |last=Makuch |first=Eddie |date=February 12, 2013 |website=GameSpot |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=February 8, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"kinectsports\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/kinect-sports-scores-3-million-sales-dance-central-sells-25-million/1100-6330113/|title= Kinect Sports scores 3 million sales, Dance Central sells 2.5 million|publisher=Gamespot|last=Sinclair|first=Brendan|date=2011-08-19|accessdate=2015-04-22}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| The ''Kinect'' series of games includes many different games which utilize [[motion controls]] by way