s-microsoft-studios-gears-of-war/|publisher=Xbox Wire|author=Xbox Wire Staff|date=2014-01-27|title=Microsoft Studios acquires rights to Gears of War franchise|accessdate=2014-01-27}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.statista.com/statistics/516581/best-selling-video-game-xbox-one-global-unit-sales/|title=Best-selling Xbox One games by unit sales 2016 {{!}} Statistic|website=Statista|language=en|access-date=2018-08-02}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Gears of War'' is a video game franchise created by [[Epic Games]], developed and managed by [[The Coalition (company)|The Coalition]], and owned and published by Xbox Game Studios. The franchise consists of six third-person shooter video games, which has also been supplemented by comics and novels. It focuses on the conflict between humanity, the subterranean reptilian hominids known as the Locust Horde, and their mutated counterparts, the Lambent.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Rayman]]'' || [[1995 in video games|September 1, 1995]] ||26 million<ref name=\"ubisoftgroup\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Rayman'' is a franchise of platform video games, published by Ubisoft. Created in 1995 by French graphic artist [[Michel Ancel]], the main character of the series, [[Rayman (character)|Rayman]], became an official mascot of its publisher, Ubisoft. The ''Rayman'' series does not include the ''Raving Rabbids'' series.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| style=\"background:#FFFFBF;\"| ''[[Tom Clancy's Rainbow Six]]'' || [[1998 in video games|August 21, 1998]] || 26 million<ref name=\"ubisoftgroup\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Rainbow Six'' is a media franchise created by American author Tom Clancy about a fictional international counter-terrorist unit called \"Rainbow\". The franchise began with Clancy's novel ''[[Rainbow Six (novel)|Rainbow Six]]'', which was adapted into a series