]]<ref name=\"yugioh\">{{cite web|url=http://edgar.secdatabase.com/1290/119312505146876/filing-main.htm |title=KONAMI CORPORATION, Form 20-F, Filing Date Jul 22, 2005 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =May 15, 2018}}</ref> || 21.8 million<ref name=\"yugioh\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| Based on the Japanese [[anime]] and [[manga]] franchise {{nihongo foot|''Yu-Gi-Oh!''|\u904a\u2606\u622f\u2606\u738b|Y\u016bgi\u014d|extra=lit. \"Game King\"|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} created by [[Kazuki Takahashi (manga artist)|Kazuki Takahashi]]. All related [[video game]]s are produced by [[Konami]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[List of Spider-Man video games|Spider-Man]]'' || [[1982 in video games|1982]] || 21.2 million<ref name=\"nyfranchises\">{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/20/technology/20game.html | title=In Video Games, Sequels Are Winners | accessdate=2009-03-21 | work=The New York Times | date=2004-09-20 | author=Eric A. Taub}}</ref>{{sfn|Makucha|2019}}{{sfn|Valentine|2019}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| Numerous electronic games featuring the popular [[Marvel Comics]] [[superhero]] ''[[Spider-Man]]'' have been released. To date, Spider-Man has made appearances on over 15 gaming platforms, which also includes mobile games on cellphones.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Imagine (video game series)|Imagine]]'' || [[2007 in video games|February 21, 2007]] || 21 million<ref name=\"ubisoftgroup\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Imagine'' is a series of [[video game]]s by [[Ubisoft]], aimed primarily at girls aged 6 to 14 released from 2007 onwards.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Total War (video game series)|Total War]]'' || [[2000 in video games|June 13, 2000]] || 21 million<ref name=\"twar\">{{cite web | url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2016-08-04