ly owned and published by [[Activision]]. The series stars the video game character [[Spyro the Dragon (character)|Spyro]], a purple European dragon. The franchise expanded to several other platforms including portable and mobile applications.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Tales (video game series)|Tales]]'' || [[1995 in video games|December 15, 1995]] || 20 million<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vitale |first1=Adam |title=Bandai Namco's 'Tales of' series surpasses 20 million total sales |url=https://www.rpgsite.net/news/8468-bandai-namco-s-tales-of-series-surpasses-20-million-total-sales |website=RPG Site |accessdate=21 July 2019 |date=8 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| The {{nihongo foot|''Tales''|\u30c6\u30a4\u30eb\u30ba|Teiruzu|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} series is a media franchise of [[role-playing video game]]s created by [[Namco Tales Studio|Wolf Team]] and formerly published by [[Namco]]. The series is currently developed and published by [[Bandai Namco Entertainment]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Mass Effect]]'' || [[2007 in video games|November 20, 2007]] || 20 million<ref>Berman, Nat. [https://moneyinc.com/how-much-is-the-mass-effect-video-game-franchise-worth/ \"How Much is the Mass Effect Franchise Worth?\"]. Money Inc. October 2018.</ref><ref name=\"mass_effect\">At least 2.5 million physical copies of [[Mass Effect: Andromeda|Mass Effect Andromeda]] sold-in as of May 2017, and over 349,000 PC digital copies sold-through as of March 2017; total figure is unknown.\n* 2.5 million copies sold-in of May 2017: {{cite web|last=Ciaccia|first=Chris|title=5 ETFs to Buy If You Love EA's Fourth-Quarter Earnings|url=https://www.thestreet.com/story/14114720/1/5-etfs-to-buy-if-you-love-ea-s-fourth-quarter-earnings.html|accessdate=11 January 2019|date=14 May 2017}}\n* 349,000+ PC digital copies sold as of March 2019: {{c