4, 2006]] || 20 million<ref name=\"ubipress 2019\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Raving Rabbids'' is a Party video games and a spin-off to [[Rayman]] developed and published by [[Ubisoft]].\n|-\n|}\n\n== At least 10 million copies ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:33.4%;\"| [[list of video game franchises|Franchise name]]\n! style=\"width:33.3%;\"| Original release date\n! style=\"width:33.3%;\"| Sales\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]]'' || February 1, 1989 || 19.1 million<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/theyre-back-playmates-toys-launches-all-new-teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-toys-76318872.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215124944/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/theyre-back-playmates-toys-launches-all-new-teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-toys-76318872.html|title=They're Back!! Playmates Toys Launches All-New Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles Toys|agency=[[PR Newswire]]|archivedate=February 15, 2017|date=October 17, 2002|accessdate=June 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.next-gen.biz/news/ubisoft-annual-sales-rise-24 |title=Ubisoft Annual Sales Rise 24% |author=Kris Graft |publisher=Next-Gen.biz |date=2007-04-26 |accessdate=2007-12-14 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815200143/http://www.next-gen.biz/news/ubisoft-annual-sales-rise-24 |archivedate=August 15, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| A video game franchise based on the [[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles|Media Franchise of the Same Name]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Driver (series)|Driver]]'' || [[1999 in video gaming|June 30, 1999]] || 19 million<ref name=\"ubisoftgroup\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Driver'' is a series of mission-based driving video games for [[PlayStation]], [[PlayStation 2]], [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]], [[Wii]], [[PlayStation Portable]], [[Game Boy Advance]],