12/0510.pdf#page=7 | archive-date=June 17, 2012 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Total ''Bemani'' franchise sales as of March 2012: 11 million + 3.61 million + 1.2 million = 15.81 million\n* Franchise sales from April 2012 to June 2012: 0.03 million\n* Total ''Bemani'' franchise sales as of June 2012: 15.81 million + 0.03 million = 15.84 million\n|group=n|name=Bemani}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| The ''[[Bemani]]'' franchise was created by [[Konami]]'s [[music video game]] division. It began with ''[[Beatmania]]'' in 1997 and was then expanded with other [[arcade game|arcade]] [[rhythm game]] series such as ''[[Dance Dance Revolution]]'', ''[[Guitar Freaks]]'', and ''[[Drum Mania]]''.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Backyard Sports series|Backyard Sports]]'' || [[1997 in video gaming|October 24, 1997]] || 15 million<ref name=\"backyard\">{{cite press release | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUS148471+21-Oct-2008+PRN20081021 | archive-url=https://archive.today/20130201052910/http://www.reuters.com/article/idUS148471+21-Oct-2008+PRN20081021 | url-status=dead | archive-date=2013-02-01 | title=Backyard Football '09 Kicks Off to North American Retailers | date=2008-10-21 | accessdate=2009-03-21 | publisher=[[Atari]] }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Backyard Sports'' is a series of video games that play on both [[video game console|consoles]] and [[computer]]s. The series is best known for starring kid-sized versions of popular professional sports stars, such as [[Albert Pujols]], [[Paul Pierce]], [[Barry Bonds]], [[Tim Duncan]], [[Kevin Garnett]], [[Tom Brady]], [[Alex Rodriguez]], [[Joe Thornton]] and [[Andy Macdonald (skateboarding)|Andy Macdonald]]. The Backyard Sports series is the only game brand licensed by all the leading professional US sports leagues ([[Major League Baseball|MLB]], [[National Basketball Association|NBA]], [[National Football League|NFL]], [[National Hockey League|NHL]], and [[Major League Soccer|MLS]]).\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Family Stadium|Famista]]'' || [[1986 in video gaming|December 10, 1986]] || 15 million<ref>{{cite web |title=FAMISTA 30TH ANNIVERSARY |url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/308/G030858/20160608008/ |website=4Gamer |publisher=BANDAI NAMCO Entertainment, Inc. |accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| {{nihongo foot|''Famista''|\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u30b9\u30bf|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}}, previously known as ''Family Stadium'', is a baseball video game franchise published by [[Bandai Namco Entertainment]]. The series began with ''Pro Baseball: Family Stadium'' on the Nintendo Family Computer in 1986, and has since expanded onto several home consoles, handhelds and mobile phones, the latest being ''Pro Baseball: Famista Evolution'' for the Nintendo Switch in 2018.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Template:Barbie video games|Barbie]]'' || 1984 || 15 million<ref name=\"barbie\">{{cite press release | url=http://www.gamingnexus.com/FullNews/Im-a-Barbie-girl-in-a-Barbie-world/Item1878.aspx | publisher=[[Activision]] | date=2006-05-23 | accessdate=2009-03-21 | title=Activision Publishing Signs Exclusive Worldwide Distribution Deal with Mattel; Activision to Distribute All New Video Games Based on Successful Barbie(R) Entertainment}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| Based on the ''[[Barbie]]'' doll made by [[Mattel]], the video games are currently published by [[Activision]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Burnout (series)|Burnout]]'' || November 11, 2001 || 15 million<ref name=\"burnout\">{{cite web | url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/new-burnout-paradise-dlc-videos | author=Ellie Gibson | title= New Burnout Paradise DLC videos News | accessdate=2009-03-21 | website=[[Eurogamer]] | date=2008-04-07}}<