lone]] [[Assassination|assassin]] who is sent to silently kill the world's most powerful criminals.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Soulcalibur (series)|Soulcalibur]]'' || [[1995 in video gaming|December, 1995]] || 15 million<ref>[https://www.famitsu.com/news/201809/13164002.html Famitsu] 2018-09-13</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| The {{nihongo|''Soulcalibur'' series|\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u30ad\u30e3\u30ea\u30d0\u30fc \u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba |S\u014drukyarib\u0101 shir\u012bzu}}, or commonly known as {{nihongo|''Soul series''|\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb \u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba |S\u014dru shir\u012bzu}} is a weapon-based [[fighting game|fighting]] video game franchise set in a [[historical fantasy]] version of the late 16th and early 17th centuries. There are seven main installments of video games and various media [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]]s, including music albums and a series of [[manga]] books. Originally released as the [[arcade game]], ''[[Soul Edge]]'', in 1995 and later ported to [[video game console]]s, more recent versions have been released for consoles only and have evolved to include online playing modes. Developed by [[Namco]] until Soul Calibur II, then by [[Project Soul]], and owned by [[Bandai Namco Entertainment]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Just Cause (video game series)|Just Cause]]'' || September 22, 2006 || 15 million<ref>[http://www.hd.square-enix.com/jpn/ir/library/pdf/ar_2018_06feature.pdf] square-enix.com</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''Just Cause'' is an action-adventure video game series created by [[Avalanche Studios]]. The series currently consists of four games, ''[[Just Cause (video game)|Just Cause]]'', ''[[Just Cause 2]]'', ''[[Just Cause 3]]'', and ''[[Just Cause 4]]''. The games are open world and take place in tropical environments.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n