ent, online leaderboards and customizable game options.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[EA Sports NASCAR series]]'' || October 31, 1997 || 9 million<ref name=\"nascar\">{{cite press release | url=http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1013893&newsId=20030916005405&newsLang=en | title=Art imitates life: EA introduces \"Grudges and Alliances,\" where the competition reacts to hard- driving | publisher=[[Electronic Arts]] | date=2003-09-16 | accessdate=2009-03-21 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710163620/http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1013893&newsId=20030916005405&newsLang=en | archivedate=2011-07-10 }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''EA Sports NASCAR series'' was a series of [[List of NASCAR video games|NASCAR video games]] published by [[EA Sports]]. The series began with [[NASCAR 98]] and [[NASCAR 99]] in 1997 and 1998, respectively. EA Sports then released NASCAR Thunder 2002 in 2001, and ever since then, [[Jeff Gordon]] (2002), [[Dale Earnhardt, Jr.]] (2003), and [[Tony Stewart]] (2004) were on the cover. After [[NASCAR Kart Racing]] was released in 2009 for the [[Wii]], EA's contract with NASCAR has since expired.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Payday: The Heist]]'' || [[2008 in video gaming|October 18, 2011]] || 9 million<ref name=\"payday\">{{cite web |url=http://www.vg247.com/2015/03/25/payday-2-and-payday-the-heist-have-sold-over-9-million-units-combined/ |title=PayDay 2 and PayDay: The Heist have sold over 9 million units combined |date=2015-03-25 |author=Nunneley, S |website=[[VG247]] |accessdate=2015-03-27}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''Payday: The Heist'' is a downloadable cooperative first-person shooter video game developed by Overkill Software and published by Sony Online Entertainment. ''Payday 2''