r.com/q9ZW8qB.gif archive])</ref>\n** DS Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon Nintendo August 2008- 252 309<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** DS Fire Emblem hero - a mystery - light and shadow of New coat of arms Nintendo  2010/07/15- 250 592<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** GBA Fire Emblem: The Sacred Stones Nintendo 2004/10/07- 233 280<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** GBA Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade Nintendo 2002/03/29- 345 574<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** GBA Fire Emblem Flame Sword Nintendo 2003/04/25- 265 286<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** GC Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance Nintendo 2005/04/20- 156 413<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** SFC Fire Emblem Thrace 776 Nintendo 1999/08/28- 145 600<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** SFC Fire Emblem: Genealogy of the Holy War Nintendo 1996/05/14- 429 763<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n** Wii Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn Nintendo 2007/02/22- 171 924<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n* 3DS Fire Emblem Awakening Nintendo 2012/04/19- 1.9M<ref name=\"Awakening and Fates sales\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2017/02/01/fire-emblem-fans-mostly-20s-30s-sales-fire-emblem-heroes/|title=Fire Emblem Fans Are Mostly In Their 20s and 30s, More On Sales And Fire Emblem Heroes|date=2017-02-01|website=Siliconera|access-date=2019-01-16}}</ref>\n* 3DS Fire Emblem Fates Nintendo 2015/06/15- 1.6M<ref name=\"Awakening and Fates sales\"/>\n* Switch Fire Emblem: Three Houses Nintendo 2019/07/26- 2.29M<ref>https://www.4gamer.net/games/999/G999905/20191105122/</ref>\n}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| {{nihongo foot|''Fire Emblem''|\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30a2\u30fc\u30a8\u30e0\u30d6\u30ec\u30e0|Fai\u0101 Emuburemu|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} is a [[fantasy]] [[tactical role-playing game]] franchise developed by [[Intelligent Systems]] and published by [[Nintendo]]. First produced and published for the [[Nintendo Entertainment System|Family Computer]] (Famicom), the series consists of fifteen main games and three [[spin-off (media)|spin-offs]]. Described by its creators as a \"[[role-playing game]] simulation\", the gameplay revolves around tactical movement of characters across grid-based environments, while incorporating a story and characters similar to traditional role-playing video games.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Inazuma Eleven (series)|Inazuma Eleven]]'' || August 22, 2008 || 8 million<ref>{{cite web|title=Inazuma Eleven Ares announced|url=http://gematsu.com/2016/07/inazuma-eleven-ares-announced|website=gematsu.com|accessdate=10 October 2017|date=2016-07-27}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| {{nihongo foot|''Inazuma Eleven''|\u30a4\u30ca\u30ba\u30de\u30a4\u30ec\u30d6\u30f3|Inazuma Irebun|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}} is a [[Role-playing video game|role-playing]] [[sports game|sports]] game franchise created by Level-5.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Cars (video game)|Cars]]'' || June 6, 2006 || 8 million<ref name=\"cars\">{{cite press release | url=http://investor.thq.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=96376&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1004548 | title=Disney/Pixar Cars Video Game from THQ Crosses the Finish Line to Prestigious Sales Milestones | date=2007-05-21 | accessdate=2009-03-21 | publisher=[[THQ]] | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120093128/http://investor.thq.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=96376&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1004548 | archive-date=2016-01-20 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''Cars'' is a [[video game]] based on the [[Disney]]/[[Pixar]] film, ''[[Cars (film)|Cars]]'', it serves as a non-canon sequel to it.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Zoo Tycoon (series)|Zoo Tycoon]]'' ||October 17, 2001 || 8 million<ref name=\"zootycoon\">{{cite press release | url=http://www.bluefang.com/press-releases/blue-fang-games-launches-its-first-iphone-game | title=Blue Fang Games Launches Its First iPhone Game | accessdate=2009-08-17 | 