ot.com/articles/valve-readying-half-life-2-bundles-counter-strike-source-available-next-week/1100-6109232/ \"Valve readying Half-Life 2 bundles; Counter-Strike: Source available next week.\"]  Gamespot. September 29, 2004.</ref>\n* ''Counter-Strike: Global Offensive'': 25 million<ref>Richard Scott-Jones. [https://www.pcgamesn.com/counter-strike-global-offensive/csgo-bestselling-pc-game-minecraft \"With 25 million sold, is CS:GO the bestselling game on PC?\"].  October 26, 2016. Accessed April 12, 2019. Total was tabulated ''prior'' to the game transitioning to free-to-play.</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Counter-Strike'' is a series of [[tactical shooter|tactical]] first-person shooter games that began as a [[Mod (video gaming)|mod]] for the game ''[[Half-Life (video game)|Half-Life]]''. The series has since been developed by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]], and published by [[Sierra Entertainment]] and Valve.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Far Cry (series)|Far Cry]]'' || [[2004 in video games|March 23, 2004]] || 50 million<ref name=\"ubisoft 2019\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Far Cry'' is a first-person shooter video game franchise originally developed by [[Crytek]], later by [[Ubisoft Montreal]] and published by [[Ubisoft]].\n|-\n|}\n\n== At least 20 million copies ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:33.4%;\"| [[list of video game franchises|Franchise name]]\n! style=\"width:33.3%;\"| Original release date\n! style=\"width:33.3%;\"| Sales\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Mortal Kombat]]'' || [[1992 in video games|October 8, 1992]] || 49 million<ref>[http://www.gamespot.com/articles/as-mortal-kombat-x-arrives-entire-franchise-reache/1100-6426616/ As Mortal Kombat X Arrives, Entire Franchise Reaches 35 Million Units Sold], [[GameSpot]] (April 14, 2015)</ref><ref>[https://www.videogamer.com/news/mortal-kombat-x-has-sold-nearly-11-million-copies MKX with nearly 1