a.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1013897&newsId=20071120005375&newsLang=en | title=EA Ships Medal Of Honor Airborne For The PlayStation 3 To Store Shelves Nationwide | date=2007-11-20 | accessdate=2009-03-21 | publisher=[[Electronic Arts]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710163602/http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1013897&newsId=20071120005375&newsLang=en |archivedate=2011-07-10}}</ref>\n* [[Medal of Honor (2010 video game)|''Medal of Honor'' (2010)]]: 5 million<ref>{{cite web|title=Electronic Arts Reports Q3 FY11 Financial Results|url=http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1012492&newsId=20110201007369&newsLang=en|website=EA.com|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|accessdate=23 August 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110208174536/http://news.ea.com/portal/site/ea/index.jsp?ndmViewId=news_view&ndmConfigId=1012492&newsId=20110201007369&newsLang=en|archivedate=8 February 2011|date=1 February 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/medal-of-honor-hot-pursuit-ship-5-million/1100-6297121/ |title=Medal of Honor, Hot Pursuit ship 5 million |website=GameSpot |date=1 February 2011 |accessdate=3 February 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302073519/http://www.gamespot.com/articles/medal-of-honor-hot-pursuit-ship-5-million/1100-6297121/ |archivedate=2 March 2014}}</ref>\n* ''[[Medal of Honor: Warfighter]]'': 3 million<ref>[http://www.gamespot.com/articles/analyst-medal-of-honor-warfighter-shipped-3-million-copies/1100-6402070/ Analyst: Medal of Honor: Warfighter shipped 3 million copies] by Eddie Makuch on January 7, 2013</ref>\n|group=n|name=Medal}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" | ''Medal of Honor'' is a series of first-person shooter games with most of the games set during [[World War II]]. The series is published by Electronic Arts.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\" |\n|- style=\"text-ali