es\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Devil May Cry'' is a series of video games set in the modern day, created by [[Hideki Kamiya]] and developed by [[Capcom]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Prince of Persia]]'' || [[1989 in video games|October 3, 1989]] || 20 million<ref name=\"ubisoftgroup\" />\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Prince of Persia'' is a [[video game franchise]] created by [[Jordan Mechner]], originally developed and published by [[Br\u00f8derbund]], then [[The Learning Company]], and currently [[Ubisoft]]. The franchise is built around a series of action-adventure games focused on various incarnations of the eponymous [[Prince (Prince of Persia)|prince]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Castlevania]]'' || [[1986 in video games|September 26, 1986]] || 20 million<ref name=\"castlevania\">{{cite web | url=http://www.gamedaily.com/articles/features/project-51-to-explore-castlevania-storyline/69268/?biz=1 | title=Project 51 to Explore Castlevania Storyline | accessdate=2009-03-21 | date=2006-08-04 | author=Chris Marlowe | publisher=GameDaily}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Castlevania'' is a [[video game series]] created and developed by [[Konami]] originally released as {{nihongo foot|''Akumaj\u014d Dracula''|\u60aa\u9b54\u57ce\u30c9\u30e9\u30ad\u30e5\u30e9|Akumaj\u014d Dorakyura|lit. \"Devil's Castle Dracula\"|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}}. The franchise spawned a number of [[action figure]]s and a Netflix series.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Frogger]]'' || [[1981 in video games|June 5, 1981]] || 20 million<ref name=\"frogger\">{{cite press release | publisher=[[Konami]] | url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/6135485.html | title=Konami's Frogger and Castlevania Nominated for Walk of Game Star | date=2005-10-11 | accessdate=2009-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n| colsp