merly published by [[Namco]]. The series is currently developed and published by [[Bandai Namco Entertainment]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Mass Effect]]'' || [[2007 in video games|November 20, 2007]] || 20 million<ref>Berman, Nat. [https://moneyinc.com/how-much-is-the-mass-effect-video-game-franchise-worth/ \"How Much is the Mass Effect Franchise Worth?\"]. Money Inc. October 2018.</ref><ref name=\"mass_effect\">At least 2.5 million physical copies of [[Mass Effect: Andromeda|Mass Effect Andromeda]] sold-in as of May 2017, and over 349,000 PC digital copies sold-through as of March 2017; total figure is unknown.\n* 2.5 million copies sold-in of May 2017: {{cite web|last=Ciaccia|first=Chris|title=5 ETFs to Buy If You Love EA's Fourth-Quarter Earnings|url=https://www.thestreet.com/story/14114720/1/5-etfs-to-buy-if-you-love-ea-s-fourth-quarter-earnings.html|accessdate=11 January 2019|date=14 May 2017}}\n* 349,000+ PC digital copies sold as of March 2019: {{cite web|last=Fischer|first=Tyler|date=April 28, 2017|title=SuperData Digital Sales March 2017: Ghost Recon Wildlands Tops Sales Charts; Market Increases 7% Year-on-Year|url=https://www.dualshockers.com/superdata-digital-sales-march-2017-ghost-recon-wildlands-tops-sales-market-increases/|publisher=DualShocker|accessdate=September 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fool.com/investing/general/2014/07/05/what-ea-must-do-to-make-mass-effect-4-a-blockbuste.aspx|title=What EA Must Do to Make 'Mass Effect 4' a Blockbuster -- The Motley Fool|first=Leo|last=Sun|publisher=}}. 14+ million copies of the first three games sold as of June 2017.</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Mass Effect'' is a series of sci-fi [[third-person shooter|third-person]] [[action role-playing game]]s developed by the Canadian company [[BioWare]] Edmonton.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[SimCity]]