-12-30 }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\"| ''Left 4 Dead'' is a series of [[cooperative gameplay|cooperative]] [[first-person shooter]] video games produced by [[Valve Corporation|Valve]].\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Tomodachi Collection]]'' || June 9, 2009 || 10.21 million shipped<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2013/04/24/this-week-in-sales-tomodachi-collection-sees-big-launch-sales/|title=This Week In Sales: Tomodachi Collection Sees Big Launch Sales|date=24 April 2013|publisher=}}</ref><ref>http://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2014/141029e.pdf</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/3ds.html |title = IR Information : Financial Data - Top Selling Title Sales Units - Nintendo 3DS Software}}</ref><ref>https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/3ds.html</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''Tomodachi Collection'' is a [[life simulation]] [[video game]] series developed and published by [[Nintendo]], originally released in June 2009 for the ''[[Nintendo DS]]''. The games are about players watching over the more-than-often ridiculous lives of their Mii characters, as they go about and perform daily activities, make friendships, and start romantic relationships. A sequel for the ''[[Nintendo 3DS]]'' called ''[[Tomodachi Life]]'' was released in 2013 in Japan, and 2014 worldwide.\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[List of One Piece video games|One Piece]]'' ||July 19, 2000 || 10.16{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bandainamcoent.co.jp/corporate/press/release/61/pdf/en_20150928.pdf|title=BANDAI NAMCO ENTERTAINMENT INC.|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2016/05/media-create-sales-5916-51516|title=Media Create Sales: 5/9/16 \u2013 5/15/16|date=2016-05-18|website=Gematsu|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite