ake-Two Interactive]] (and what is now [[2K Play]]). The games consists of various mini-games with a [[Funfair|carnival]] theme.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Watch Dogs]]'' || [[2014 in video gaming|May 27, 2014]] || 8 million shipped<ref name=\"ubisoftgroup\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''Watch Dogs'' (stylized as  ''WATCH_DOGS'') is an [[action-adventure game]] developed by [[Ubisoft Montreal]] and published by [[Ubisoft]]. It was released for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]], and [[Wii U]] in 2014. Set in a fictionalized version of [[Chicago]], the plot follows [[Hacker (computer security)|hacker]] Aiden Pearce's search for revenge after the killing of his niece. The game is played from a [[Virtual camera system#Third-person view|third-person perspective]], and the world is navigated on foot or by vehicle. An [[online multiplayer]] mode allows up to eight players to engage in [[Cooperative gameplay|cooperative]] and competitive gameplay.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Ninja Gaiden]]'' || [[1988 in video gaming|December 9, 1988]] || 7.705 million{{#tag:ref|''Ninja Gaiden'' series:\n* Series sales as of June 2007: 5.5 million<ref name=\"tecmofranchises\">{{cite web | url=http://www.tecmo.co.jp/company/data/20070823cp_e.pdf#page=13 | title=TECMO Corporate Profile (as of June 2007) | page=12 | format=PDF | accessdate=2008-01-07 | publisher=[[Tecmo]] | date=August 23, 2007}}</ref>\n* Sales from June 2007 to December 2008: 2.205 million<ref>{{cite web|title=Financial Statements Summary for Fiscal Year Ended December 2008|url=http://www.tecmo.co.jp/company/data/20090216gaikyo_e.pdf#page=5|publisher=[[Tecmo]]|accessdate=22 April 2012|page=4|date=February 16, 2009}}</ref>\n|name=NinjaGaiden|group=n}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| {{nihongo foot|''Ninja Gaiden''|\u5fcd\u8005\u5916\u4f1