 Studios]] and [[Sega]]. This series is exclusive to the [[Dreamcast]], [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]] and [[Xbox 360]] consoles only. This series of racing games consists of ''[[Metropolis Street Racer]]'', ''[[Project Gotham Racing (video game)|Project Gotham Racing]]'', ''[[Project Gotham Racing 2]]'', ''[[Project Gotham Racing 3]]'', and ''[[Project Gotham Racing 4]]''.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Unreal (video game series)|Unreal]]'' || [[1998 in video gaming|May 22, 1998]] || 7 million<ref name=\"unreal\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.midway.com/us/pr/mpr_4478.html |title=Midway announces Unreal Anthology coming Fall 2006 |date=2006-06-15 |accessdate=2009-03-21 |publisher=[[Midway Games|Midway]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081116003141/http://www.midway.com/us/pr/mpr_4478.html |archivedate=November 16, 2008 }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| The ''Unreal'' series is a [[video game]] [[media franchise|franchise]] developed by Epic MegaGames, now known as [[Epic Games]] and originally published by [[GT Interactive]], later by [[Infogrames]], [[Atari]], and currently by [[Midway Games]]. It was powered by the [[Unreal Engine technology|Unreal Engine]] which had been in development for over three years before the game was released.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#e6e9ff; height:3px;\"|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| ''[[Trine (video game)|Trine]]'' || [[2009 in video gaming|July 3, 2009]] || 7 million<ref name=\"Trine Sales\">{{cite web|url=http://www.joystiq.com/2014/10/16/trine-series-tops-7-million-sales-shares-its-level-editor|title=Trine series tops 7 million sales, shares its level editor|first=Jessica|last=Conditt|publisher=Joystiq|date=October 16, 2014|accessdate=October 16, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''Trine'' is an action-platform and puzzle game developed by [[Frozenbyte]] that takes place in a medieval fantasy setting and allows p